bananas and crohn's disease i seem to get a bit of a reaction whenever i eat bananas and no other type of food does anyone with crohn's have this problem i know i have ulcers at the beginning of my small bowel but bananas seem to be the only thing that bothers them hi generous i am a crohns patient as well what we eat will vary in each person will affect us differently as well for instance i can't eat anything that is hard to digest like asparagus lettuce nuts popcorn brussel sprouts etc if you go to the crohn's colitis foundation of america's site you can find alot of information on diet medications exercise surgery and even locate a support group near you where you can meet others like yourself they also have an online chat as well as a toll free number m f am am est where you can talk to health care professionals well versed in ibd crohns ulcerataive colitis if certain foods are a problem ask your md for a referral to see a registered dietician at a local clinic or hospital the site i provided below will also help you locate an rd who works by themselves in your town be sure that you are taking your meds faithfully going to your md appts not smoking or drinking as it will really aggrivate the disease and eating healthy when you are not in pain best of health to you from one crohnie to anohter Ulcerative colitis Inflammatory bowel disease Diarrhea Stomach cancer Folic acid Prostate cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Colorectal cancer Fecal incontinence Hypoglycemia Medicine Adjustable gastric band Coeliac disease Raw food diet Obesity Diabetes mellitus Nutrition Insulin Autistic enterocolitis Hamster Food Andrew Wakefield Pneumonia Multiple sclerosis Escherichia coli O157:H7 Chronic fatigue syndrome Tocopherol Clinical depression Dietary fiber Cardiovascular disease Migraine Gastroesophageal reflux disease Growth hormone Publicly funded medicine Dietitian Pig (zodiac) Fistula Ankylosing spondylitis Race in biomedicine Mouth ulcer Ileostomy Dieting Physician Breastfeedi